Interface Transcriber<T extends Activator>

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AnjiNetTranscriber, ESHyperNEATTranscriberBain, HyperNEATTranscriber, HyperNEATTranscriberBain, HyperNEATTranscriberBainBase, HyperNEATTranscriberGridNet, NEATTranscriberBain, TranscriberAdaptor

    public interface Transcriber<T extends Activator>
    To "transcribe" is to construct a phenotype from a genotype.
    Author:
    Philip Tucker

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      java.lang.Class getPhenotypeClass() 
      T transcribe(Chromosome c)
      Sub-classes must implement this method to convert the genotype to a phenotype.
      T transcribe(Chromosome c, T substrate)
      Sub-classes must implement this method to convert the genotype to a phenotype, using an existing substrate object to allow performance gains by avoiding destroying and creating large objects or arrays.
